      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/7/7",
      "text": [
        ": قُلْتُ لِأَبِي جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ أَصْلَحَكَ اَللَّهُ مَا أَيْسَرُ مَا يَدْخُلُ بِهِ اَلْعَبْدُ اَلنَّارَ قَالَ «مَنْ أَكَلَ مِنْ مَالِ اَلْيَتِيمِ دِرْهَماً وَ نَحْنُ اَلْيَتِيمُ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1650 - It is narrated from Abu Basir, who said:\nI asked Abu Ja’far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) \"May Allah (swt) keep you well, what is the simplest way for a person to enter the Fire?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"Whoever consumes a dirham from the wealth of the orphan - and we are the orphan.\""
        ]
      }
    },
